
###############################################################
# Example .env for Sanity CMS integration
#
# 1. Visit https://www.sanity.io/manage to create/find your project.
# 2. Copy your Project ID and Dataset name below.
# 3. API version is usually '2023-01-01' (see docs for updates).
# 4. Set USE_CDN=true for public/production, false for preview/dev.
# 5. Save and restart your dev server after editing this file.
#
# Troubleshooting:
# - If you see a warning in the console about missing env vars, check these values.
# - Restart your dev server after any .env changes.
# - See src/sanity/env.ts for validation and setup guidance.
#
# Example values for dev/staging/prod:
#
# DEV:
# VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your-dev-project-id
# VITE_SANITY_DATASET=development
# VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
# VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=false
#
# STAGING:
# VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your-staging-project-id
# VITE_SANITY_DATASET=staging
# VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
# VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=true
#
# PROD:
# VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your-prod-project-id
# VITE_SANITY_DATASET=production
# VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
# VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=true
#
###############################################################
VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_SANITY_DATASET=
VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=true

###############################################################
# Setup Instructions
###############################################################
# 1. Copy this file to `.env` in your project root.
# 2. Fill in your Sanity project ID and dataset.
# 3. Restart your dev server after changes.
# 4. Visit https://www.sanity.io/manage to find your project ID and dataset.
# 5. See https://www.sanity.io/docs for more help.

###############################################################
# Troubleshooting & Validation
###############################################################
# - If you see '[Sanity] Missing environment variables' in the console, check your .env file and restart the dev server.
# - To validate your setup, run:
#     npx envinfo --system --env
# - Common issues:
#   * Project ID or dataset missing: Check spelling and copy from Sanity dashboard.
#   * API version outdated: Use a recent YYYY-MM-DD value (see docs).
#   * CDN issues: Set VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=false for local development if needed.
# - For advanced config (staging, production), duplicate this file as `.env.staging` or `.env.production` and set variables accordingly.

###############################################################
# Example Configurations
###############################################################
# Development:
#   VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your-dev-project-id
#   VITE_SANITY_DATASET=development
#   VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
#   VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=false
#
# Production:
#   VITE_SANITY_PROJECT_ID=your-prod-project-id
#   VITE_SANITY_DATASET=production
#   VITE_SANITY_API_VERSION=2023-01-01
#   VITE_SANITY_USE_CDN=true

###############################################################
# API Versioning & CDN Notes
###############################################################
# - Use the latest API version for new features and best performance.
# - The CDN is recommended for public sites; disable for local/private data.
# - See https://www.sanity.io/docs/api-versioning and https://www.sanity.io/docs/cdn for details.
